---
import BaseHead from '../../components/BaseHead.astro';

const title = 'Jack Maguire — Paid Social Director for CMOs';
const description = 'I fix broken paid social measurement (CAPI, Pixel, conversion signal) and turn it into revenue. 12 years, $30M+ managed spend, $10M+ profitable revenue driven. Available now.';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={title} description={description} />
		<script type="application/ld+json">
		{
			"@context": "https://schema.org",
			"@type": "ProfilePage",
			"mainEntity": {
				"@type": "Person",
				"name": "Jack Maguire",
				"jobTitle": "Paid Social Director",
				"url": "https://jackmaguire.org/cmo/",
				"sameAs": ["https://www.linkedin.com/in/paidsocialdirector/"]
			}
		}
		</script>
	</head>
	<body>
		<main>
			<section class="hero">
				<div class="wrap">
					<p class="eyebrow">Paid social leadership &middot; available now</p>
					<h1>Your paid social funnel is probably reporting numbers it can't back up.</h1>
					<p class="subhead">
						Most teams find out during a platform update, a privacy change, or a board
						question they can't answer cleanly. I've spent 12 years being the person brought
						in to find the leak, rebuild the measurement layer, and put the budget back to work
						on signal that's actually true.
					</p>
					<a href="#contact" class="cta-link">See how, then book a call &darr;</a>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="signal-diagram-section">
				<div class="wrap">
					<h2>What "broken" usually looks like, and what fixing it does</h2>
					<div class="diagram" role="img" aria-label="Diagram showing a broken measurement pipeline of ad platform, degraded pixel and CAPI signal, blind targeting, and wasted spend, transforming into a fixed pipeline of rebuilt CAPI and pixel, clean signal, validated targeting, and profitable revenue.">
						<div class="pipeline broken">
							<span class="pipeline-label">Before</span>
							<div class="stage" data-state="broken"><span class="stage-name">Ad platform</span></div>
							<div class="connector broken-connector" aria-hidden="true"></div>
							<div class="stage" data-state="broken"><span class="stage-name">Degraded Pixel / CAPI signal</span></div>
							<div class="connector broken-connector" aria-hidden="true"></div>
							<div class="stage" data-state="broken"><span class="stage-name">Algorithm optimizing on noise</span></div>
							<div class="connector broken-connector" aria-hidden="true"></div>
							<div class="stage" data-state="broken end"><span class="stage-name">Spend scaled on a broken read</span></div>
						</div>
						<div class="pipeline fixed">
							<span class="pipeline-label">After</span>
							<div class="stage" data-state="fixed"><span class="stage-name">Ad platform</span></div>
							<div class="connector fixed-connector" aria-hidden="true"></div>
							<div class="stage" data-state="fixed"><span class="stage-name">Rebuilt Pixel + CAPI, clean signal</span></div>
							<div class="connector fixed-connector" aria-hidden="true"></div>
							<div class="stage" data-state="fixed"><span class="stage-name">Targeting validated with holdout tests</span></div>
							<div class="connector fixed-connector" aria-hidden="true"></div>
							<div class="stage" data-state="fixed end"><span class="stage-name">$10M+ in profitable revenue</span></div>
						</div>
					</div>
					<p class="diagram-caption">
						This is the actual sequence: fix the measurement first, because you can't scale a
						funnel you can't measure. Everything after that (targeting, creative, holdout
						tests) only works once the input data is trustworthy.
					</p>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="proof-section">
				<div class="wrap">
					<h2>The numbers, from doing this work for 12 years</h2>
					<div class="stat-grid">
						<div class="stat">
							<span class="stat-number">$30M+</span>
							<span class="stat-label">ad spend managed</span>
						</div>
						<div class="stat">
							<span class="stat-number">300K+</span>
							<span class="stat-label">leads generated</span>
						</div>
						<div class="stat">
							<span class="stat-number">$10M+</span>
							<span class="stat-label">profitable revenue driven</span>
						</div>
						<div class="stat">
							<span class="stat-number">250M+</span>
							<span class="stat-label">monthly impressions managed</span>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="case-note">
						<p>
							<strong>National Debt Relief, 2022 to 2026.</strong> Led Meta and TikTok paid
							social offline conversion events, Conversions API, and Pixel integrations,
							working directly with engineering to repair degraded signal quality in a
							regulated industry. Layered on regression and ML (random forest, neural nets,
							decision trees) to confirm which signals actually mattered, added third-party
							audience integrations via Oracle and LiveRamp coordinated through Salesforce,
							and ran holdout market tests to validate incrementality before scaling spend.
							Result: an estimated $5M of the $10M+ in profitable revenue came directly from
							that measurement rebuild.
						</p>
						<p>
							Managed $1M+ in monthly ad spend, led a team of paid social managers, and drove
							300,000+ Facebook followers and 365,000+ email leads over the role.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="fit-section">
				<div class="wrap">
					<h2>What I'm looking for</h2>
					<p>
						Director-level or adjacent paid social / performance leadership, ideally in
						financial services, consumer finance, DTC, or another data-driven team where the
						measurement layer actually matters to the business. Open to remote or NYC-based.
					</p>
					<p>
						If your team is scaling spend on a funnel nobody fully trusts, or you've got a paid
						social leadership seat open and want someone who starts with the data, that's the
						conversation I want to have.
					</p>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section id="contact" class="contact-section">
				<div class="wrap">
					<h2>Get in touch</h2>

					<div class="calendly-slot">
						<p class="calendly-label">Book 30 minutes directly</p>
						<p class="calendly-note">
							Fastest way to talk. Pick a time that works and I'll be there.
						</p>
						<a href="https://calendly.com/jpmaguire2/30min" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="calendly-btn">
							Book a call &rarr;
						</a>
					</div>

					<p class="or-divider">Or send a message and I'll follow up personally</p>

					<form id="cmo-form" action="https://api.web3forms.com/submit" method="POST">
						<input type="hidden" name="access_key" value="0d5ededb-778b-452f-b8f0-72ebb2e4e461" />
						<input type="hidden" name="subject" value="New lead from jackmaguire.org/cmo" />
						<input type="hidden" name="from_name" value="jackmaguire.org CMO landing page" />
						<input type="checkbox" name="botcheck" class="botcheck" style="display:none" />

						<div class="form-row">
							<label for="name">Name<span class="req">*</span></label>
							<input type="text" id="name" name="name" required autocomplete="name" />
						</div>

						<div class="form-row">
							<label for="email">Work email<span class="req">*</span></label>
							<input type="email" id="email" name="email" required autocomplete="email" />
						</div>

						<div class="form-row two-col">
							<div>
								<label for="company">Company</label>
								<input type="text" id="company" name="company" autocomplete="organization" />
							</div>
							<div>
								<label for="role">Your role</label>
								<input type="text" id="role" name="role" placeholder="e.g. CMO, VP Marketing" />
							</div>
						</div>

						<div class="form-row">
							<label for="message">Message</label>
							<textarea id="message" name="message" rows="4" placeholder="What's the role, or what's broken?"></textarea>
						</div>

						<button type="submit" class="submit-btn">Send</button>
						<p class="form-note">No spam. I read every message myself and reply directly.</p>
						<p class="form-error" role="alert" hidden>
							Something went wrong sending that. Please email
							<a href="mailto:maguirebaseball@gmail.com">maguirebaseball@gmail.com</a> directly instead.
						</p>
					</form>

					<script>
						const form = document.getElementById('cmo-form');
						if (form instanceof HTMLFormElement) {
							form.addEventListener('submit', async (event) => {
								event.preventDefault();
								const errorEl = form.querySelector('.form-error');
								const submitBtn = form.querySelector('.submit-btn');
								if (submitBtn instanceof HTMLButtonElement) {
									submitBtn.disabled = true;
									submitBtn.textContent = 'Sending...';
								}
								if (errorEl instanceof HTMLElement) errorEl.hidden = true;

								try {
									const response = await fetch(form.action, {
										method: 'POST',
										headers: { Accept: 'application/json' },
										body: new FormData(form),
									});
									const result = await response.json();
									if (result.success) {
										window.location.href = '/cmo/thank-you/';
										return;
									}
									throw new Error(result.message || 'Submission failed');
								} catch (err) {
									if (errorEl instanceof HTMLElement) errorEl.hidden = false;
									if (submitBtn instanceof HTMLButtonElement) {
										submitBtn.disabled = false;
										submitBtn.textContent = 'Send';
									}
								}
							});
						}
					</script>
				</div>
			</section>
		</main>
	</body>
</html>

<style>
	:global(body) {
		background: var(--paper);
	}
	main {
		max-width: none;
		padding: 0;
	}
	.wrap {
		max-width: 760px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 0 1.25em;
	}

	.hero {
		padding: 3.5em 0 2.5em;
		border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(85, 107, 47, 0.18);
	}
	.eyebrow {
		font-family: var(--font-ui), sans-serif;
		font-size: 0.72rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: var(--accent-dark);
		text-transform: uppercase;
		letter-spacing: 0.06em;
		margin: 0 0 0.75em;
	}
	.hero h1 {
		font-family: var(--font-heading), sans-serif;
		font-size: clamp(1.6em, 5.5vw, 2.5em);
		line-height: 1.18;
		margin: 0 0 0.75em;
		color: rgb(var(--black));
	}
	.subhead {
		font-size: 1.08em;
		line-height: 1.6;
		color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
		max-width: 620px;
		margin: 0 0 1.5em;
	}
	.cta-link {
		display: inline-block;
		font-family: var(--font-ui), sans-serif;
		font-weight: 700;
		font-size: 0.95em;
		color: var(--accent-dark);
		text-decoration: none;
		border-bottom: 2px solid var(--accent);
		padding-bottom: 2px;
	}
	.cta-link:hover {
		color: var(--accent);
	}

	.signal-diagram-section {
		padding: 3em 0;
		background: var(--paper-warm);
		border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(85, 107, 47, 0.18);
	}
	.signal-diagram-section h2 {
		font-size: clamp(1.15em, 4vw, 1.5em);
		margin: 0 0 1.5em;
	}
	.diagram {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 1.5em;
	}
	.pipeline {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		gap: 0;
		position: relative;
		padding-top: 1.4em;
	}
	.pipeline-label {
		position: absolute;
		top: 0;
		left: 0;
		font-family: var(--font-ui), sans-serif;
		font-size: 0.68rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		letter-spacing: 0.06em;
		color: rgb(var(--gray));
	}
	.stage {
		font-family: var(--font-ui), sans-serif;
		font-size: 0.78rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		padding: 0.6em 0.85em;
		border-radius: 6px;
		line-height: 1.3;
		max-width: 160px;
	}
	.stage[data-state='broken'] {
		background: transparent;
		border: 1.5px dashed #b3492f;
		color: #b3492f;
	}
	.stage[data-state='fixed'] {
		background: var(--accent);
		border: 1.5px solid var(--accent-dark);
		color: #fff;
	}
	.connector {
		flex: 0 0 auto;
		width: 1.75em;
		height: 0;
		border-top: 2px solid;
		margin: 0 -1px;
	}
	.broken-connector {
		border-top-style: dashed;
		border-top-color: #b3492f;
	}
	.fixed-connector {
		border-top-style: solid;
		border-top-color: var(--accent-dark);
	}
	.diagram-caption {
		margin-top: 1.5em;
		font-size: 0.92em;
		color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
		line-height: 1.55;
		max-width: 620px;
	}

	.proof-section {
		padding: 3em 0;
		border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(85, 107, 47, 0.18);
	}
	.proof-section h2 {
		font-size: clamp(1.15em, 4vw, 1.5em);
		margin: 0 0 1.25em;
	}
	.stat-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
		gap: 1em;
		margin-bottom: 2em;
	}
	.stat {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 0.2em;
		padding: 1em 0.25em;
		border-top: 3px solid var(--accent);
	}
	.stat-number {
		font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Menlo', 'Consolas', monospace;
		font-size: 1.5em;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: rgb(var(--black));
	}
	.stat-label {
		font-size: 0.78em;
		color: rgb(var(--gray));
	}
	.case-note {
		background: var(--paper-warm);
		border-radius: 8px;
		padding: 1.4em 1.5em;
		font-size: 0.95em;
		line-height: 1.6;
	}
	.case-note p {
		margin: 0 0 1em;
	}
	.case-note p:last-child {
		margin-bottom: 0;
	}

	.fit-section {
		padding: 3em 0;
		border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(85, 107, 47, 0.18);
	}
	.fit-section h2 {
		font-size: clamp(1.15em, 4vw, 1.5em);
		margin: 0 0 1em;
	}
	.fit-section p {
		max-width: 620px;
		line-height: 1.6;
	}

	.contact-section {
		padding: 3em 0 4em;
	}
	.contact-section h2 {
		font-size: clamp(1.15em, 4vw, 1.5em);
		margin: 0 0 1.25em;
	}
	.calendly-slot {
		border: 1.5px solid var(--accent);
		border-radius: 8px;
		padding: 1.5em;
		margin-bottom: 1.25em;
		background: var(--paper-warm);
	}
	.calendly-label {
		font-family: var(--font-ui), sans-serif;
		font-weight: 700;
		font-size: 1.05em;
		margin: 0 0 0.35em;
		color: rgb(var(--black));
	}
	.calendly-note {
		font-size: 0.9em;
		color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
		margin: 0 0 1em;
		line-height: 1.5;
	}
	.calendly-btn {
		display: inline-block;
		font-family: var(--font-ui), sans-serif;
		font-weight: 700;
		font-size: 0.95em;
		background: var(--accent-dark);
		color: #fff;
		text-decoration: none;
		border-radius: 6px;
		padding: 0.75em 1.75em;
	}
	.calendly-btn:hover {
		background: var(--accent);
	}
	.or-divider {
		font-family: var(--font-ui), sans-serif;
		font-size: 0.8em;
		font-weight: 700;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		letter-spacing: 0.04em;
		color: rgb(var(--gray));
		text-align: center;
		margin: 0 0 1.5em;
	}

	form {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 1.1em;
	}
	.form-row {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 0.4em;
	}
	.form-row.two-col {
		flex-direction: row;
		gap: 1em;
	}
	.form-row.two-col > div {
		flex: 1;
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 0.4em;
	}
	label {
		font-family: var(--font-ui), sans-serif;
		font-size: 0.85em;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
	}
	.req {
		color: #b3492f;
		margin-left: 0.15em;
	}
	input[type='text'],
	input[type='email'],
	textarea {
		font-family: Verdana, Tahoma, Geneva, sans-serif;
		font-size: 1em;
		padding: 0.65em 0.75em;
		border: 1.5px solid rgb(var(--gray-light));
		border-radius: 6px;
		background: #fff;
		color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
	}
	input:focus,
	textarea:focus {
		outline: 2px solid var(--accent);
		outline-offset: 1px;
		border-color: var(--accent);
	}
	textarea {
		resize: vertical;
	}
	.submit-btn {
		align-self: flex-start;
		font-family: var(--font-ui), sans-serif;
		font-weight: 700;
		font-size: 0.95em;
		background: var(--accent-dark);
		color: #fff;
		border: none;
		border-radius: 6px;
		padding: 0.75em 2em;
		cursor: pointer;
	}
	.submit-btn:hover {
		background: var(--accent);
	}
	.form-note {
		font-size: 0.78em;
		color: rgb(var(--gray));
		margin: 0.25em 0 0;
	}
	.form-error {
		font-size: 0.85em;
		color: #b3492f;
		margin: 0.25em 0 0;
	}
	.submit-btn:disabled {
		opacity: 0.7;
		cursor: not-allowed;
	}

	@media (max-width: 640px) {
		.stat-grid {
			grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
		}
		.form-row.two-col {
			flex-direction: column;
		}
		.pipeline {
			flex-direction: column;
			align-items: flex-start;
		}
		.connector {
			width: 0;
			height: 1.25em;
			border-top: none;
			border-left: 2px solid;
			margin: -1px 0;
			margin-left: 1.1em;
		}
		.broken-connector {
			border-left-style: dashed;
			border-left-color: #b3492f;
			border-top: none;
		}
		.fixed-connector {
			border-left-style: solid;
			border-left-color: var(--accent-dark);
			border-top: none;
		}
		.stage {
			max-width: none;
		}
	}
</style>
